Simple Shell Manual (hsh)

NAME
    hsh - simple UNIX command interpreter

SYNOPSIS
    hsh
    echo "command" | hsh

DESCRIPTION
    The hsh program is a simple shell that reads input, parses commands,
    handles built-in functions, resolves commands using the PATH environment
    variable, and executes external programs using fork and execve.

FEATURES
    - Interactive and non-interactive modes
    - Built-in commands: exit, env
    - Command execution through fork/execve
    - PATH resolution
    - Error handling and correct exit status

BUILT-INS
    exit
        Exit the shell with the last returned status.

    env
        Print the current environment variables.

EXAMPLES
    Interactive mode:
        ./hsh
        :) ls
        :) exit

    Non-interactive mode:
        echo "ls -l" | ./hsh

EXIT STATUS
    The shell returns the status of the last executed command.
    Returns 127 if the command is not found.

AUTHORS
